reviewed.","The performance options with Pirelli is its biggest downside. Using Pirelli&#39;s tire finder tool, I searched for the three most popular tire sizes fitting 15-, 16- and 17-inch rims. I also searched for the six most popular truck tire sizes fitting rims between 16- and 18-inches. Despite having 20 tire performance series, Pirelli averaged only one option for the 15-inch rim. On the 16-inch rim, the 205/55R16 tire had ten options, but the 215/70R16 had no options and the 225/60R16 had only four options. In addition, the 17-inch rim averaged just five options.","However, Pirelli&#39;s truck tires are practically nonexistent, at least as it applies to popular truck sizes. Despite having a section for Light Truck tires on the website, none of the six popular truck tire sizes had any performance options to fit. This isn&#39;t entirely surprising, considering Pirelli&#39;s reputation as a high-performance race tire.","<strong>Summary</strong><br/>Pirelli is a high-performance tire brand with excellent tread-life warranties. The average pricing is more competitive than you might think for a brand famous for making tires for super cars, but they&#39;re still more expensive than the average tire. The biggest downside to Pirelli is the limited performance options."]},"id":"112ebb7c-3ebd-4ad2-94b7-e43dd837d288","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_58241","url":"/pirelli-p4-four-seasons-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"jeph-preece","url":"/author/jeph-preece","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","name":"Jeph Preece","dateModified":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","id":"UEqrRM5xmXnCHCjkbS6o5e","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2013-11-19T20:23:27Z","datePublished":"2013-11-19T20:23:27Z","name":"Pirelli","synopsis":"Pirelli is an Italian tire brand founded in 1872, making it one of the oldest tire brands in the world. It's mostly famous for its high-performance tires made for super